{"meta":{"domain":"subjects","kid":"5107","authors":[{"fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre","id":"6"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:23 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:23 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"body":"<p class=\"Paragraph\">There is an ancient morphological verb opposition in Tibetan which corresponds to a causative derivation. This morphological opposition has generated verb pairs: a \u201ccausative\u201d verb, both transitive and volitional, is derived<a href=\"#_ftn1\">[1]<\/a> from a basic verb which is usually both intransitive and non-volitional. This basic verb stem is referred to here as the \u201cresultative\u201d form.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">The two verbs that comprise each pair are phonetically very close, and in most cases their pronunciation differs only in <em>terms <\/em>of tone or <em>aspiration<\/em>.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">The causative derivation is essential in many Tibeto-Burman languages as well as in Classical Tibetan (with over 200 verb pairs) and in some archaic dialects of Amdo, but in Central Tibetan and in the Standard Spoken language, it applies only to a few dozen verbs.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f45\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo break\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f46\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo break\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f99\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo lay\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f49\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo lie\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f40\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo stop\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f42\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo stop\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f66\u0fb3\u0f44\u0f66\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo raise\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f63\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo rise\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f51\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo scatter\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f50\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo scatter, be scattered\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo boil\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo boil\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo stir, turn\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo stir, turn\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f4f\u0f7c\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo take out\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f51\u0f7c\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo go out\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f55\u0f56\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo bring down, take down\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f56\u0f56\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo descend, get down\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f92\u0fb2\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo free\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0fb2\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo be freed\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f51\u0f56\u0fb2\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo tear\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo tear\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f45\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo cut\u201d (causative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f46\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cTo be cut\u201d (resultative)<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">Compared to the basic resultative stem, the causative always has an additional argument corresponding to an <strong>intentional agent <\/strong>performing the action.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">If the resultative is intransitive, the causative is transitive.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">If the resultative is transitive, the causative is ditransitive (see the examples below).<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">It emerges from the above that all the <strong>causative verbs are transitive and volitional<\/strong>, since they imply an agent is intentionally performing an action on an object or a patient. Resultative verbs are usually intransitive and non-volitional.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f50\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f0d<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe rope broke.\u201d (The rope got cut by itself, without any intentional cause.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f50\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f45\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f0d<\/span> Causative: \u201cHe cut the rope.\u201d (An agent cut the rope intentionally.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f64\u0f7a\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f92\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5e\u0f42<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe pane broke.\u201d (The pane broke by itself, without any intentional cause.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0fa4\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f7c\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f64\u0f7a\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f92\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f45\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f0d<\/span> Causative: \u201cThe children broke the pane.\u201d (The children intentionally broke the pane.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f4e\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0fa1\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5e\u0f42<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe prayer wheel is still spinning.\u201d (Nobody is now making it spin, it is spinning by itself.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0fa8\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f4e\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f0d<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe old lady has turned the prayer wheel.\u201d (An agent has intentionally turned the wheel.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f61\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5e\u0f42<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe letter is torn.\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f56\u0fb2\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> Causative: \u201cHe tore the letter (intentionally).\u201d<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">Certain resultative intransitive verbs may, in some cases, allow the use of an unintentional agent.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5e\u0f42<\/span> Resultative: \u201cHe tore the letter (unintentionally).\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0fa4\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f7c\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f64\u0f7a\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5e\u0f42<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe children broke the pane (unintentionally).\u201d <\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">However, this construction is rather rare in Standard Spoken Tibetan. Some speakers prefer to use other constructions such as the sentence below which has a similar meaning:<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0fa4\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f7c\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f5f\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f5f\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f59\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f64\u0f7a\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5e\u0f42<\/span> \u201cBecause the children were not careful, the pane broke.\u201d<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">The resultative verbs include a few intransitive volitional and transitive volitional forms. In such cases, the corresponding causative verbs have a supplementary actant that itself acts on another agent.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0fa4\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f55\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f7c\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe child herself put on her <em>chuba<\/em>.\u201d <\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f68\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fa4\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f55\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> Causative: \u201cThe mother put the <em>chuba <\/em>on the child.\u201d (ditransitive) (Note that this is a very formal register; in the conversational language, the verb <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f61\u0f7c\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b<\/span> would be used.)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0fa8\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f50\u0f74\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f74\u0f42<\/span> Resultative: \u201cThe old lady can\u2019t get up.\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f44\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa8\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0fb3\u0f44\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0d<\/span> Causative: \u201cI helped the old lady to get up.\u201d<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">Causative and resultative verbs can appear in the same sentence. The causative puts emphasis on <strong>the cause of the process and the effort of the agent<\/strong> in performing the action, while the resultative verb is concerned only with <strong>the result or the consequence <\/strong>of that action. Such constructions may therefore be translated by using the verbs \u201cto succeed,\u201d \u201cto manage,\u201d \u201ccan,\u201d or other modal expressions.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">These constructions, which frequently occur in the literary language, also appear in the spoken language.<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f66\u0f94\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f55\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f53\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f44\u0f7c\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f53\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f56\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cAfter the <em>ngakpa <\/em>had (performed a ritual) to make rain fall, rain did indeed fall!\u201d<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f62\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f54\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb2\u0f7c\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f41\u0fb2\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f74\u0f42 \u0f42\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f56\u0fb2\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f53\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f74\u0f42<\/span> \u201cThis cloth is very strong, I can\u2019t tear it!\u201d (Literally: \u201cHowever much I [try to] tear it, it won\u2019t tear.\u201d)<\/li> <\/ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">The following examples are taken from literary texts:<\/p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f56\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7a\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f74\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb1\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f5f\u0f74\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f74\u0f42<\/span> \u201cEven if one rubs, one cannot rub out the undrawn lines on the heart.\u201d (Causative: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f74\u0f56\u0f0b<\/span>; Resultative: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f5f\u0f74\u0f56\u0f0b<\/span>)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f53\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f7a\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5f\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f5f\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f55\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f5e\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f5f\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f45\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f55\u0f7a\u0f53\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cIf you try to control your own mind inside and you don\u2019t succeed, then what\u2019s the use of catching somebody else\u2019s body outside.\u201d (Causative: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f5f\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span>; Resultative: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f5f\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b<\/span>)<\/li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f4c\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f9f\u0f7a\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f61\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f5e\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f7c\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f5e\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f4f\u0f7a\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f50\u0f7a\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f0d<\/span> \u201c(Once), he (saw) a mouse trying to move a turquoise that was on his ma\u1e47\u1e0dala. But the mouse could not lift the jewel on its own, so\u2026\u201d (Causative: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f4f\u0f7a\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span>; Resultative: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f50\u0f7a\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span>)<\/li> <\/ul><p>\u00a0<\/p><hr size=\"1\" \/><p><a href=\"#_ftnref1\">[1]<\/a> Many of the causative verbs were formed by a morpheme <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66<\/span> attached to the verb. This is still visible in the Tibetan orthography: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> (resultative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> (causative); <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f49\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> (resultative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f99\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> (causative); <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f63\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span> (resultative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0fb3\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span> (causative); <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f41\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b<\/span> (resultative), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b<\/span> (causative), etc.<\/p>","title":""}]}
